HEADWORD: Hummer
<hw>Hum"mer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, hums; one who applauds by humming.</def>
<rj><au>Ainsworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A humming bird.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Humming</ent>⟦br⟧
